<main>
    <section>
        <h2>Memory & Storage</h2>

        <div class="columns">
            <article>
                <h3>RAM (Memory)</h3>

                <img src="/img/ram.png" alt="RAM Memory">

                <p>
                    Random Access Memory, or RAM, is where a computer keeps information
                    it needs while programs are open. Having more RAM helps your computer
                    handle several programs at once without slowing down.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article>
                <h3>Storage (SSD / HDD)</h3>

                <img src="/img/storage.png" alt="Computer Storage">

                <p>
                    Storage devices like Solid-State Drives (SSD) and Hard Disk Drives
                    (HDD) keep the operating system, programs, and your files saved,
                    even when the computer is off.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

